</ul>

<hr class="datasources-hr" />

<h5>World Development Indicators (WDI) published by the World Bank</h5>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Data:</strong> GDP and GNI (gross national income) constructed and corrected for price differences (across time and countries) in different ways</li>
 	<li><strong>Geographical coverage:</strong> Global â€“ by country and world region</li>
 	<li><strong>Time span:</strong> The earliest data is available for 1960.</li>
 	<li><strong>Available at:</strong> The different measures are published as part of the <a href="http://data.worldbank.org/data-catalog/world-development-indicators">World Development Indicators</a>. The data on current GDP in US-$ is <a href="http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.CD">here</a>.</li>
</ul>

